        </div>

        <div class="inline-cta">
          <div class="cta-copy">
            <h4>Want SEO that runs itself — not another dashboard?</h4>
            <p>theStacc handles research, briefs, writing, on-page optimisation, and publishing to your CMS. <strong>SEO content shipped weekly for $99/mo</strong> — strategy approved by you, execution handled.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cta-action">
            <a href="/demo/" class="cta-btn-inline">See a live demo <span>→</span></a>
            <span class="cta-meta">No card · 15-min walkthrough</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 id="what-is">What "SEO autopilot" actually means in 2026</h2>
        <p>The phrase covers three very different products. Map yourself to the layer you need before reading reviews:</p>

        <ol>
          <li><strong>Technical autopilot</strong> — Alli AI. Push on-page changes (titles, schema, internal links) to live pages on a schedule.</li>
          <li><strong>Content autopilot</strong> — theStacc, Byword, Journalist AI. Research, write, optimise, and publish articles end-to-end.</li>
          <li><strong>Platform autopilot</strong> — Search Atlas OTTO, SE Ranking. Bundle several automations with reporting in a single seat.</li>
        </ol>

        <div class="callout callout-warn">
          <div class="callout-label">The autopilot trap</div>
          <p>Most "autopilot" tools still need you to brief, edit, approve, and publish. If a tool's autopilot mode produces drafts that sit in a queue waiting on you, it is an assistant, not an autopilot. Test the publish step before you commit — that is where 80% of platforms quietly hand the work back.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="how-we-tested">How we tested all 10 tools</h2>
        <p>Same brief, same sites, same 90-day window.</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Test sites</strong> — 3 fresh domains in SaaS, ecom, and local service.</li>
          <li><strong>Scope</strong> — run each tool in its most-hands-off mode, measure operator hours required.</li>
          <li><strong>Measurement</strong> — articles or fixes shipped without human input, time saved, indexing rate, all-in cost.</li>
          <li><strong>Total spend</strong> — $2,140 across 10 tools, Mar–May 2026.</li>
        </ul>

